00:44:56.527 --> 00:44:58.696
A big round of applause. please.

524
00:45:01.573 --> 00:45:03.909
Thank you.

525
00:45:06.704 --> 00:45:11.625
The host just gave
such a wonderful introduction

526
00:45:11.709 --> 00:45:13.502
that I'm honestly overwhelmed.

527
00:45:14.294 --> 00:45:18.966
I didn't expect so many of you to come.
but thanks to you. filling up the seats.

528
00:45:19.466 --> 00:45:22.845
I feel like I've become
a best-selling author.

529
00:45:23.929 --> 00:45:25.431
Call me delusional. but hey.

530
00:45:25.514 --> 00:45:29.017
I'll work hard to become
a best-selling author. maybe.

531
00:45:30.436 --> 00:45:31.979
-Right. so today膩聙娄
-You're here.

532
00:45:32.062 --> 00:45:34.398
I'd like to extend my heartfelt gratitude膩聙娄

533
00:45:34.481 --> 00:45:35.858
Where's Hyeon-suk?

534
00:45:35.941 --> 00:45:39.528
膩聙娄to you all for coming all this way
to attend the launch of my book.

535
00:45:39.611 --> 00:45:42.656
-<i>Designing a Sustainable Future</i>.
-They're not coming today.

536
00:45:42.740 --> 00:45:45.701
-Something urgent came up.
-I'm truly humbled by your support.

537
00:45:45.784 --> 00:45:46.744
Thank you so much.

538
00:45:53.000 --> 00:45:54.668
Why didn't you tell me?

539
00:45:56.003 --> 00:45:58.714
You should have told me
you were sick sooner.

540
00:46:00.340 --> 00:46:03.260
I didn't want you to worry.

541
00:46:05.095 --> 00:46:08.390
I'm okay now. Don't worry.

542
00:46:08.891 --> 00:46:13.437
Please. how can I not worry?
Do you know how scared I was?

543
00:46:15.606 --> 00:46:19.151
Please don't get sick anymore. okay?

544
00:46:20.277 --> 00:46:21.695
Okay.

545
00:47:21.880 --> 00:47:23.674
<i>I thought everything would be over</i>

546
00:47:24.174 --> 00:47:26.218
<i>once I buried that secret.</i>

547
00:47:26.885 --> 00:47:28.136
<i>But it wasn't.</i>

548
00:47:29.721 --> 00:47:32.891
Yun. what are you doing? Come out here.

549
00:47:34.184 --> 00:47:35.644
Jeong-hu's leaving.

550
00:47:54.037 --> 00:47:55.664
What's wrong. Yun?

551
00:47:59.293 --> 00:48:00.919
Are you not feeling well?

552
00:48:04.548 --> 00:48:07.968
Are you still upset about
what happened to Min-hui?

553
00:48:14.558 --> 00:48:16.518
How long are you going to keep this up?

554
00:48:17.352 --> 00:48:19.313
I have my limits too.

555
00:48:19.396 --> 00:48:21.565
Get up. Kim Se-yun.

556
00:48:21.648 --> 00:48:24.359
Now. Listen to your mother!

557
00:48:27.362 --> 00:48:28.989
They've already had her funeral.

558
00:48:29.072 --> 00:48:32.284
It's all over. When are you going to
stop acting like a child?

559
00:48:32.367 --> 00:48:34.661
What do you mean. it's over?

560
00:48:36.580 --> 00:48:38.332
You have no idea. Mom.

561
00:48:41.251 --> 00:48:42.711
You don't know.

562
00:48:43.712 --> 00:48:45.631
You don't know anything.

563
00:48:45.714 --> 00:48:50.302
<i>That was when it all truly began.</i>

564
00:48:53.472 --> 00:48:54.806
Oh my God!

565
00:49:01.396 --> 00:49:02.397
You膩聙娄

566
00:49:07.444 --> 00:49:08.737
You were there?

567
00:49:09.404 --> 00:49:10.530
I saw it.

568
00:49:12.491 --> 00:49:13.617
I saw everything.

569
00:49:14.993 --> 00:49:16.662
What Dad did.

570
00:49:17.913 --> 00:49:19.623
Look. she's bleeding! My God.

571
00:49:19.706 --> 00:49:20.916
Can you move?

572
00:49:24.211 --> 00:49:26.838
-She's alive.
-She is.

573
00:49:30.342 --> 00:49:32.761
Please step aside.

574
00:49:43.397 --> 00:49:44.564
Please step aside.

575
00:49:44.648 --> 00:49:46.566
She's unconscious. Oh dear.

576
00:49:47.859 --> 00:49:48.986
Okay. let's lift her.

577
00:49:49.069 --> 00:49:50.654
Three. two. lift!

578
00:49:53.365 --> 00:49:55.117
Three. two. one.

579
00:49:55.200 --> 00:49:56.493
Let's move.

580
00:49:57.828 --> 00:49:58.745
<i>Min-hui</i>

581
00:49:59.329 --> 00:50:03.000
<i>was definitely conscious then.</i>

582
00:50:20.684 --> 00:50:22.644
Please keep tailing that car.

583
00:50:37.325 --> 00:50:39.202
Come on. sir.

584
00:50:53.133 --> 00:50:55.552
She was conscious when brought in.
What happened?

585
00:50:55.635 --> 00:50:58.180
I'm not sure.
I stepped out for a moment. and膩聙娄

586
00:50:58.263 --> 00:51:00.182
-Get ready to perform CPR.
-Will do.

587
00:51:08.065 --> 00:51:10.150
-Please page the clinical fellow.
-Sure.

588
00:51:11.109 --> 00:51:12.944
No pulse. She's in cardiac arrest.

589
00:51:13.028 --> 00:51:14.654
Start compressions. Now.

590
00:51:14.738 --> 00:51:16.656
Starting compressions. now!

591
00:51:32.923 --> 00:51:34.674
-Epinephrine every three minutes.
-Yes.

592
00:51:35.258 --> 00:51:37.844
-Intubate her as soon as we're ready.
-Understood.

593
00:52:04.079 --> 00:52:04.996
So膩聙娄

594
00:52:08.250 --> 00:52:10.127
So. your housekeeper膩聙娄

595
00:52:11.628 --> 00:52:13.088
With your own two hands膩聙娄

596
00:52:25.642 --> 00:52:27.018
No. Yun.

597
00:52:29.604 --> 00:52:31.022
Not yet.

598
00:52:33.108 --> 00:52:34.568
Nothing is certain.

599
00:52:34.651 --> 00:52:37.988
No. it was Dad's car.
It was definitely Dad!

600
00:52:40.115 --> 00:52:42.242
Dad did something to her.

601
00:52:46.121 --> 00:52:47.122
My baby.

602
00:52:52.043 --> 00:52:53.753
I hoped you'd never find out.

603
00:53:02.637 --> 00:53:03.513
Mom.

604
00:53:05.265 --> 00:53:06.600
How did you膩聙娄

605
00:53:10.187 --> 00:53:11.646
How long have you known?

606
00:53:15.483 --> 00:53:16.443
Yun.

607
00:53:17.903 --> 00:53:20.030
That's not important right now.

608
00:53:21.698 --> 00:53:24.075
Stop crying and listen to me.

609
00:53:25.118 --> 00:53:27.704
We now have to find out

610
00:53:28.330 --> 00:53:29.331
what Dad really did膩聙娄

611
00:53:31.208 --> 00:53:33.001
for ourselves.

612
00:53:36.046 --> 00:53:37.172
How?

613
00:53:45.513 --> 00:53:49.768
How about we go see a late-night movie
after this? It's been a while.

614
00:53:50.769 --> 00:53:51.895
A late-night movie?

615
00:53:53.313 --> 00:53:55.065
Or we could just go for a drive.

616
00:53:56.107 --> 00:53:57.400
Doesn't that sound wonderful?

617
00:53:57.484 --> 00:53:59.861
It'd be a waste to stay home
on a night like this.

618
00:53:59.945 --> 00:54:03.615
No. I can't. I have plans.
so I have to go out in a bit.

619
00:54:12.916 --> 00:54:16.253
You go to the hospital.
I'll go to the park.

620
00:54:16.336 --> 00:54:18.088
When I meet your dad there.

621
00:54:18.838 --> 00:54:21.091
I'm going to question him
about everything.

622
00:54:22.050 --> 00:54:26.471
In the meantime. you have to check
the hospital's CCTV footage.

623
00:54:27.514 --> 00:54:28.515
Got it?

624
00:55:10.849 --> 00:55:13.268
Hey. Jeong-hu.
Why are you calling me so late?

625
00:55:13.768 --> 00:55:14.728
What?

626
00:55:16.896 --> 00:55:19.274
Yun knows everything? What does he know?

627
00:55:22.902 --> 00:55:23.862
Jeong-hu.

628
00:55:24.571 --> 00:55:26.990
I have no idea what you're talking about.

629
00:55:27.574 --> 00:55:28.825
Let's meet up first.

630
00:55:29.868 --> 00:55:31.202
Let's talk in person.

631
00:55:57.354 --> 00:55:58.396
Hey. Yun.

632
00:55:59.356 --> 00:56:00.231
Did you find it?

633
00:56:00.732 --> 00:56:01.858
Did you check it?

634
00:56:14.871 --> 00:56:15.705
Se-yun.

635
00:56:21.878 --> 00:56:23.922
<i>Yun was crying.</i>

636
00:56:25.548 --> 00:56:27.550
He said the footage was useless.

637
00:56:30.261 --> 00:56:33.223
It was in a blind spot.
so he couldn't see anything.

638
00:56:38.478 --> 00:56:40.855
It's over now. It's all over.

639
00:56:41.648 --> 00:56:45.568
We lost all the evidence we could've used
to get a confession out of him.

640
00:56:48.780 --> 00:56:50.240
This is all my fault.

641
00:56:51.074 --> 00:56:53.284
I shouldn't have gotten rid of that file.

642
00:56:56.079 --> 00:56:58.706
I don't know how I'll face him
from now on.

643
00:57:01.751 --> 00:57:03.545
It's so scary. so horrifying.

644
00:57:11.219 --> 00:57:12.887
I don't know what to do now.

645
00:57:16.182 --> 00:57:19.102
How am I meant to go on living?

646
00:57:28.361 --> 00:57:29.404
Eun-joo.

647
00:57:32.365 --> 00:57:33.241
It's okay.

648
00:57:37.078 --> 00:57:38.329
I'll help you.

649
00:57:40.248 --> 00:57:41.666
I'll do whatever it takes.

650
00:57:50.383 --> 00:57:51.634
Don't worry.

651
00:58:05.231 --> 00:58:10.361
MR. HEO MUN-OH

652
00:58:26.044 --> 00:58:26.878
Lee Kang.

653
00:58:28.213 --> 00:58:29.297
Listen carefully.

654
00:58:29.964 --> 00:58:31.174
That evidence.

655
00:58:32.217 --> 00:58:33.760
We can make it ourselves.

656
00:58:35.762 --> 00:58:36.930
What do you mean by--

657
00:58:37.013 --> 00:58:39.140
<i>Just listen to me. you punk!</i>

658
00:58:41.142 --> 00:58:44.395
That night.
the night of Seon Min-hui's accident.

659
00:58:44.938 --> 00:58:47.440
You followed her to the hospital. okay?

660
00:58:48.024 --> 00:58:50.235
You followed Kim Su-hun to the hospital.

661
00:58:51.736 --> 00:58:52.570
What?

662
00:58:52.654 --> 00:58:53.905
And there.

663
00:58:54.948 --> 00:58:56.366
you witnessed it.

664
00:59:16.970 --> 00:59:19.514
You saw it with your own two eyes.

665
00:59:20.098 --> 00:59:21.349
Do you understand me?

666
00:59:22.350 --> 00:59:23.476
<i>Mr. Heo.</i>

667
00:59:24.561 --> 00:59:26.271
That will be how膩聙娄

668
00:59:28.356 --> 00:59:29.983
your story ends.

669
00:59:34.404 --> 00:59:37.407
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

